-- Orckit Falls Most Since 2002 in Tel Aviv on Deferral, Price Cut
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-02-16T11:51:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/orckit-falls-most-since-2002-in-tel-aviv-on-deferral-price-cut.html
Orckit Communications Ltd. (ORCT)  slumped
the most in almost 10 years after it reached an agreement with
Series A bondholders that includes deferring early redemption
rights and lowering the conversion price.  The  shares  tumbled 28 percent, the biggest intraday drop
since November 2002, to 2.049 shekels at 1:47 p.m. in  Tel Aviv ,
giving the company a market value of 46.6 million shekels ($12
million). The stock tumbled as much as 41 percent earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
